<abstract><t>This document defines two new IPv6 Routing header types. Generically, they are called the Compressed Routing Header (CRH). More specifically, the 16-bit version of the CRH is called the CRH- 16, while the 32-bit version of the CRH is called the CRH-32.  SRm6 nodes use the CRH to steer packets from segment to segment along SRm6 paths.</t></abstract>

